Which of the following statements are true about choosing and using a shard key?

Options are :
1. There must be a index on the collection that starts with the shard key.
2. The shard key must be unique
3. You can change the shard key on a collection if you desire.
4. MongoDB can not enforce unique indexes on a sharded collection other than the shard key itself, or indexes prefixed by the shard key.
5. Any update that does not contain the shard key will be sent to all shards.

Answers :
1. There must be a index on the collection that starts with the shard key.
4. MongoDB can not enforce unique indexes on a sharded collection other than the shard key itself, or indexes prefixed by the shard key.
5. Any update that does not contain the shard key will be sent to all shards.

